org.kepler.sms

Class SemanticTypeDefinition

  • java.lang.Object
    • ptolemy.kernel.util.NamedObj
      • ptolemy.kernel.util.Attribute
        • ptolemy.kernel.util.ConfigurableAttribute
          • org.kepler.sms.SemanticTypeDefinition
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, Changeable, Configurable, Debuggable, DebugListener, Derivable, ModelErrorHandler, MoMLExportable, Moveable, Nameable, Settable

    public class SemanticTypeDefinition
extends ConfigurableAttribute
    A data structure to hold a semantic type given in a kar file. The property can contain a configuration (configure element), which gives the concept definition in OWL-DL. One can also give a source file, however, this functionality is not yet supported.
    Author:
    bowers
    Created:
    May 9, 2005
